<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122a1027-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1341"><num value="1341">§ 1341.</num><heading> Smithsonian Institution: report</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to the usual number of the report of the Smithsonian Institution ten thousand copies shall be printed: one thousand for the Senate, two thousand for the House of Representatives, five thousand for distribution by the Smithsonian Institution, and two thousand for distribution by the National Museum.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122a1028-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1272">82 Stat. 1272</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
